					<description><![CDATA[<p>What is Terminalia Arjuna? Terminalia Arjuna is a tree found mostly in India. It is known for its special bark, which has been used in Ayurvedic medicine for centuries. It is often called Arjuna. This tree is famous for supporting heart health, which is why it’s sometimes called the “heart tree.” The bark is the main part used for making medicine, and it’s been traditionally used to help with heart problems, high blood pressure, and cholesterol. Arjuna’s popularity in natural medicine comes from its ability to strengthen the heart and improve overall cardiovascular health. In addition to heart benefits, Arjuna </p>
<p>The post <a href="https://weclinic.in/blog/terminalia-arjuna-uses">Terminalia Arjuna &#8211; Uses, Dosage, Side Effects, Composition, And More</a> appeared first on <a href="https://weclinic.in/blog">WeClinic&trade; Blog</a>.</p>
